Copyright and derivation notice for the lame package
====================================================

Portions of this package are derived from the 'amen' package
(Additive and Multiplicative Effects Models for Networks and Relational
Data), Copyright (c) Peter D. Hoff, distributed under GPL-3:

  https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=amen

lame extends the additive and multiplicative effects framework to
longitudinal and bipartite networks. Several of its Gibbs samplers and
numerical helpers were taken from, or adapted from, the corresponding
routines in amen. Because amen is licensed under GPL-3, lame is
distributed under GPL-3 as well.

Files containing code written by or derived from Peter Hoff carry an
`@author Peter Hoff` tag in their roxygen documentation. As of this
version that covers 33 files under R/ and one under src/, including the
following routines whose implementations remain substantially those of
amen:

  ldZgbme, llsrmRho, raSab_bin_fc, raSab_cbin_fc, raSab_frn_fc,
  rbeta_ab_rep_fc, rrho_fc, rrho_mh_rep, rUV_fc, rUV_rep_fc,
  rUV_sym_fc, rwish, simY_frn, simY_ord, sm2el, zscores

All other code is Copyright (c) the lame authors (Cassy Dorff,
Shahryar Minhas, Tosin Salau), also under GPL-3.
